2. Change font to Wingdings
3. Change font size to 36

item.title: Ms word easter egg - twin towers
item.dc:creator: @Ron Ron
item.description:
@Ron wrote:

This is so old.

Also people say the name of the Airplane that crashed into the Twin Towers were Q33 NY. Which is completely retarded cause it wasn’t. Some goofy goober just played around with web dings font until he created a picture that looked like an airplane crashing into 2 towers, and as a joke he told his friend that the type of the plane was Q33 NY. And it just spread like crazy.

In reality, there are no easter eggs in Microsoft/Microsoft word, they are either accidents or remnants of stuff they were testing in the past. There was a lawsuit several months before XP was released that stated that no one who was selling their program is allowed to have special hidden things inside that are not stated! You can however have easter eggs in a program that you aren’t profitting from. Such as Ubuntu Linux or Spybot.
